Executive Profile
Jonathan J. Rubinstein  Head of The Global Business Unit, WebOSAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships60--
Background

		Mr. Jonathan J. Rubinstein, also known as Jon, served as the Head of the Global Business Unit at WebOS since July 2011. Mr. Rubinstein served as Senior Vice President of Product Innovation for Personal Systems Group at the Hewlett-Packard Company from July 2011 to January 2012. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President at Palm, Inc. from June 12, 2009 to July 2010. He served as Senior Vice President and General Manager of the Palm Global Business Unit of ... the Hewlett-Packard Company from July 2010 to July 2011. He left HP on January 27, 2012. He served as a Partner of Elevation Partners. He served as Senior Vice President of Hardware Engineering of Apple Inc. from February 1997 to 2003 and also served as its Senior Vice President of iPod Division from 2003 to March 31, 2006. He also led the team that built the iMac. He has over 25 years of industry experience. Before joining Apple, He served as an Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer at FirePower Systems from August 1993 to August 1996 and was responsible for strategic planning, engineering, manufacturing and sales and marketing. Prior to FirePower, he served as Vice President and General Manager of Hardware and Vice President of Hardware Engineering at NeXT Computer, where he was responsible for product development and instrumental in defining its new product development process. Before that, he managed processor development for the Titan Graphics Supercomputer family at Stardent Computer, as well as designed and architected portions of the Stardent 3000 and 2000 computer systems. At Hewlett Packard, Mr. Rubinstein architected the HP 9000 Series 300 family of workstations, was a Member of the Design Team for the HP 9836 workstation and helped define the engineering and pre-production test processes for new products. He served as the Executive Chairman of Palm, Inc. from October 2007 to July 2010. He has been a Director at Amazon.com, Inc. since December 16, 2010. He serves as a Member of Board of Advisors of Green Plug, Inc. Mr. Rubinstein served as a Director of QUALCOMM Incorporated since May 06, 2013 until May 04, 2016. He served as a Member of The Athletic & Scientific Advisory Board at CoolSystems Inc. He served as a Director of Immersion Corporation from October 1999 to October 2007. He served as Member of Advisory Board at Baymark Technologies Inc. He is a Member of the National Academy of Engineering. He is a Senior Member of the IEEE and a Member of the Association for Computing Machinery. Mr. Rubinstein earned a B.S. and an M.Eng in Electrical Engineering from Cornell University and an M.S. in Computer Science from Colorado State University.Read Full Background




